layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 16; written lines: 16; Uniform layout. Masoretic and other notes in the margins. Visible ruling with a mastara.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental square and semi-cursive script of approximately 15th century.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Museum from him on 08 July 1882, folio [253v].
